Splattercannon/ Hellplague:

Hellplague walked back to Celeron and sat down in the floor, shutting off the lights.  She was silent, waiting for something.

&quot;*Hellplague, we know you are in there.  Come out Traitor!  Master commands it!*&quot; a voice demands over her comm.

She shuts it off, and sighs.  She might not live through this.


rm2kmidi &lt;kraftlos@...&gt; wrote:
Celeron found some ammo to a cannon that for all he could tell, no
longer was part of the ship.  He compulsively emptied all the
cartridges and removed the gunpowder which he then quickly poured into
some jar-like containers.  He used some spare parts to create a
detonator, then some scrap metal to provide some shrapnel, finally
tightly wrapping the makeshift devices in tape.  He now had six
functional grenades that would prove very useful.  He found a little
hiding space by the main hatch where he sat and waited with his
grenades and riffle that was in less than perfect condition.  If all
else failed he would resort to using his arm cannons.

&quot;Ready!&quot; he said, doubting she could hear him.


&quot;HA!  Is that all you got?  You boasted such power, such skill!  Where is your power and skill now?  You disappoint me, ha ha ha haa!&quot; 


